    Correctly format body for the delivery status mail

[33mcommit ff27fb2cbb287db47e76cdb17565b9467dba70fa[m
Author: Jared Hancock <jared@osticket.com>
Date:   Fri Mar 27 11:22:55 2015 -0500

    email: Some bounce notices actually have rich content
    
    Here's an example email structure:
    ```
    multipart/mixed
     - multipart/report; delivery-status
       - multipart/alternative
         - text/plain
         - text/html
       - message/delivery-status
       - message/rfc822
    ```
    
    The previous code would only find the body if the email main headers had:
    Content-Type: multipart/report; report-type="delivery-status". In such a
    case it would scan for a plain/text body.
    
    This patch will scan for the usual body if the scan for the body as usual if
    the report scan did not find anything.
    
    Also, output errors to stderr when running API from the command line

[33mcommit fc1a56ea7785d62bdd22baf4f61c66f7ab1bf988[m
Author: Peter Rotich <peter@enhancesoft.com>
Date:   Fri Mar 27 15:58:50 2015 +0000

    bug: Consider list when looking up list item
    
