Date:   Wed Jul 9 10:06:11 2014 -0500

    i18n: Allow pluralization of related ticket links
    
    The terms `%d open|closed tickets` need to be made plural so that the terms
    `open` and `closed` can be properly translated.
    
    References:
    (Crowdin login required)
    http://i18n.osticket.com/translate/osticket-official/148/enus-de#3735

[33mcommit d95382f608495bd9e413c8ae4eafda5fa6a739e8[m
Author: Jared Hancock <jared@osticket.com>
Date:   Wed Jul 9 09:53:33 2014 -0500

    i18n: Allow multiple translations of "Open"
    
    The software defines at least three contexts for the phrase "Open"
    
      * The name of a ticket queue (Open tickets)
      * A status of a ticket (Open / Closed)
      * An action to be performed (Open a ticket)
    
    References:
    (Crowdin login required)
    http://i18n.osticket.com/translate/osticket-official/148/enus-de#2915

